        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Adrien Miquel writes:\n\nIt's just to tell you that there is probably a bug in Zend_Date. \n\nI'm explaining : in the framework's documentation it's said that the constant for ISO 8601 date output 'yy' describes the year with AT LEAST two digits, but in fact it describes the year with ONE OR TWO digits. This is because the format 'yy' uses the year constant Zend_Date::YEAR_SHORT (line 486 in Zend_Date.php). So, if these three lines are removed, 'yy' will effectively describes the year with at least two digits. "
        },
