        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16462",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Sorry, but I can't see the problem...\n\nWhen I code:\n{code}\n$date->toString('yy');\n{code}\nI get '09' returned...\n\nAlso the definition is 2 digit...\n{code}\n    const YEAR_SHORT     = 'YEAR_SHORT';     \/\/ y - 2 digit year, leading zeros 00-99\n{code}\nRemoving these 3 lines will cause other code to fail...\n\nPlease provide a testcode where the problem can be seen and fixed.\n\nPS: 'yy' does not return ISO8601 date but non ISO year... ISO YEAR is 'YY' !!\n\n@Bill:\nMaybe you can forward this to Adrien, when he does not have write priviledges to jira.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-08-27T15:08:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-08-27T15:08:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16490",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=hannibalbundy",
                        "name": "hannibalbundy",
                        "displayName": "Adrien Miquel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi Thomas,\n\nthe problem is that if you code :{code:xml}$date = new Zend_Date('1-1-1') ;\necho $date->toString('yy');{code}you will get returned '1' and not '01', which should be the result expected according to the Zend_Date's doc.\nThis issue affects 'yy' and 'YY' constants.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=hannibalbundy",
                        "name": "hannibalbundy",
                        "displayName": "Adrien Miquel",
